1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ESTABLISH REQUIREMENTS FOR SITING AND OPERATION OF DATA
3 CENTERS AND TO MAKE VARIOUS CHANGES TO STATE ENERGY AND
4 UTILITIES POLICY.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6
7 PART I. REQUIREMENTS FOR DATA CENTERS
8
9 REQUIREMENTS FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT APPROVAL PROCESS
10 SECTION 1.(a) Article 9 of Chapter 160D of the General Statutes is amended by
11 adding a new section to read:
12 "§ 160D-974. Site assessment required for data centers; other requirements.
13 (a) Prior to any approval of a rezoning application, special exception, conditional or
14 special use permit, or building permit for the siting of a new data center, a local government shall
15 require that an applicant:
16 (1) Perform and submit a site assessment to examine the sound profile of the data
17 center on residential units and schools located within 500 feet of the data
18 center property boundary. A locality may also require that a site assessment
19 examine the effect of the proposed facility on the community with regard to
20 (i) ground and surface water resources, (ii) air quality, (iii) thermal plumes,
21 (iv) agricultural resources, (v) parks, (vi) registered historic sites, and (vii)
22 forestland on the data center site or immediately contiguous land.
23 (2) Submit an attestation that the data center will employ a closed-loop water or
24 a liquid cooling system that will result in minimization of water consumption
25 for cooling systems to the maximum extent possible, in compliance with
26 G.S. 143-355.5A.
27 (b) The site assessment submitted to a local government pursuant to subdivision (1) of
28 subsection (a) of this section shall be used by the local government to assess consistency with
29 the policies of the local government's comprehensive plan, if any, and compliance with the local
30 government's adopted noise ordinances, zoning ordinance provisions, and other applicable laws
31 and regulations, if any.
32 (c) This section shall not apply to a site with an existing legislative, quasi-judicial, or
33 administrative approval where an applicant is seeking an expansion or modification of an already
*S730-v-5*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 existing or approved facility and such expansion does not exceed an additional monthly electrical
2 demand of 100 megawatts or more.
3 (d) For purposes of this section, the term "data center" means a facility, campus of
4 facilities, or array of interconnected facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for
5 the primary purpose of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a
6 peak monthly electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater. The term "data center" does not
7 include a facility or portion of a facility containing electronic equipment that is incidental to and
8 used in support of a business whose primary business activity is not the storing, retrieving,
9 managing, and processing of digital data.
10 (e) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit, limit, or otherwise supersede
11 existing local zoning authority."
12 SECTION 1.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
13 applications for rezoning, special exceptions, conditional or special use permits, or building
14 permits submitted on or after that date.
15
16 WATER USE STANDARDS FOR DATA CENTERS
17 SECTION 2.(a) Article 38 of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes is amended by
18 adding a new section to read:
19 "§ 143-355.5A. Water use standards for data centers.
20 (a) The Department shall adopt rules establishing water use standards for data centers to
21 ensure the protection of surface water and groundwater resources.
22 (b) The water use standards adopted by the Department: (i) may require data centers to
23 employ closed-loop or reclaimed water systems as necessary to avoid impacts to areas with water
24 availability concerns; and (ii) shall not permit a data center to use an evaporative cooling system.
25 For purposes of this subsection, an "evaporative cooling system" means any cooling system that
26 consumes water through evaporation as a primary method of heat rejection.
27 (c) For purposes of this section, the term "data center" means a facility, campus of
28 facilities, or array of interconnected facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for
29 the primary purpose of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a
30 peak monthly electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater. The term "data center" does not
31 include a facility or portion of a facility containing electronic equipment that is incidental to and
32 used in support of a business whose primary business activity is not the storing, retrieving,
33 managing, and processing of digital data."
34 SECTION 2.(b) The Department of Environmental Quality shall adopt permanent
35 rules to implement the requirements of this section no later than September 1, 2026. The rules
36 adopted shall apply only to data centers for which no local development approvals or State
37 permits, certifications, or authorizations have been issued for siting of the data center on or before
38 the date the rules become effective.
39
40 PROHIBIT CERTAIN FOREIGN OWNERSHIP OF DATA CENTERS AND LAND
41 UPON WHICH DATA CENTERS ARE SITED
42 SECTION 3.(a) Chapter 64 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
43 Article to read:
44 "Article 5.
45 "Prohibit Adversarial Foreign Government Ownership of Data Centers and Land on which Data
46 Centers are Located.
47 "§ 64-64. Definitions.
48 As used in this Article, the following definitions apply:
49 (1) Adversarial nation. – One of the following:
50 a. China.
51 b. Iran.
Page 2 Senate Bill 730-Fifth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 c. North Korea.
2 d. Russia.
3 (2) Data center. – A facility, campus of facilities, or array of interconnected
4 facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for the primary purpose
5 of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a peak
6 monthly electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater. The term "data
7 center" does not include a facility or portion of a facility containing electronic
8 equipment that is incidental to and used in support of a business whose
9 primary business activity is not the storing, retrieving, managing, and
10 processing of digital data.
11 (3) De minimis direct interest. – Any ownership of land or a data center resulting
12 from ownership of registered equities in a publicly traded company owning
13 the land or data center and if the ownership interest in the company is either
14 of the following:
15 a. Less than five percent (5%) of any class of registered equities.
16 Ownership of registered equities is determined by processes
17 established under federal law.
18 b. Less than five percent (5%) interest in an entity controlled by a
19 company that is both registered with the United States Securities and
20 Exchange Commission as an investment adviser under the Investment
21 Advisers Act of 1940, as amended, and is not a foreign entity.
22 (4) Foreign government. – Any government other than the federal government or
23 the government of a state or a political subdivision of a state.
24 (5) Interest. – Any estate, remainder, or reversion, or any portion of the estate,
25 remainder, or reversion, or an option pursuant to which one party has a right
26 to cause the transfer of legal or equitable title to land described in
27 G.S. 64-65(a), including, without limitation, a lease of land described in
28 G.S. 64-65(a) (i) for a term of one year or longer or (ii) renewable by option
29 for terms which, if the options were all exercised, would total one year or
30 longer.
31 (6) Party. – Any individual, corporation, company, association, firm, partnership,
32 society, joint-stock company, trust, estate, or any other legal entity.
33 (7) Prohibited foreign party. – Any of the following:
34 a. A citizen or resident of an adversarial nation.
35 b. A foreign government formed within an adversarial nation.
36 c. A party other than an individual or government that is created or
37 organized under the laws of a foreign government within an
38 adversarial nation.
39 d. A party other than an individual or a government that meets all of the
40 following criteria:
41 1. Is created or organized under the laws of any state.
42 2. A significant interest or substantial control is directly or
43 indirectly held or is capable of being exercised by one or more
44 of the following:
45 I. An individual referred to in sub-subdivision a. of this
46 subdivision.
47 II. A foreign government referred to in sub-subdivision b.
48 of this subdivision.
49 III. A party referred to in sub-subdivision c. of this
50 subdivision.
