1 (c) A prohibited foreign party that has acquired any interest in land described in
2 subsection (a) of this section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, in
3 this State prior to the effective date of this section may continue to own or hold that interest but
4 may not acquire by grant, purchase, devise, descent, or otherwise any additional interest in land
5 described in subsection (a) of this section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a
6 data center, in this State and must register with the Secretary of State and the Attorney General.
7 The Secretary of State and the Attorney General shall maintain one joint database of those foreign
8 parties that have registered, and the database shall be accessible and searchable by the public on
9 each agency's website. The Secretary of State and the Attorney General shall establish a
10 registration form for the purposes of this subsection, and the form shall include at least the
11 following information:
12 (1) The name of the owner of the land or the owner of the interest in the land, or
13 the owner of the data center, as applicable.
14 (2) The address of the land, the parcel identification number, and the property's
15 legal description, or the address of the data center, as applicable.
16 (3) The number of acres of the land on which the data center is located.
17 (4) The mailing address of the owner of the land or the data center, as applicable.
18 (5) Country of citizenship and residency status or country of incorporation of the
19 owner of the land or the owner of the interest in the land, or the owner of the
20 data center, as applicable.
21 (d) A prohibited foreign party that fails to timely file a registration with the Secretary of
22 State and the Attorney General pursuant to subsection (c) of this section is subject to a civil
23 penalty of not less than one thousand dollars ($1,000) for each day that the registration is late,
24 the clear proceeds of which shall be remitted to the Civil Penalty and Forfeiture Fund, in
25 accordance with G.S. 115C-457.2. The unpaid balance of any penalties assessed under this
26 subsection shall constitute a lien against the land if a lien, denoted as a Notice of Foreign
27 Ownership Violation Lien, has been recorded by the Attorney General in the office of the register
28 of deeds in the county where the property is located, and the lien shall have priority from the date
29 and time of recordation and shall be enforced by the Attorney General.
30 (e) A prohibited foreign party that acquires land described in subsection (a) of this
31 section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, on or after the effective
32 date of this section, by devise or descent, through the enforcement of security interests, or through
33 the collection of debts, other than a de minimis direct interest, shall sell, transfer, or otherwise
34 divest itself of the land within three years after acquiring the land, or the significant interest in or
35 substantial control of the data center.
36 (f) At the time of purchase, a buyer of any interest in land described in subsection (a) of
37 this section shall provide an affidavit signed under penalty of perjury attesting that the buyer is
38 (i) not a prohibited foreign party and (ii) in compliance with the requirements of this section. The
39 affidavit is not required to be notarized and shall be attached as an exhibit to the deed or other
40 document that conveys an ownership interest in the land. The failure to obtain or maintain the
41 affidavit shall not affect the title or insurability of the title for the land, and shall not result in civil
42 or criminal liability to any person or entity, unless the person or entity is in violation of subsection
43 (k) of this section herein, or subject any nonparty to the purchase to civil or criminal liability,
44 unless a nonparty to the purchase has actual knowledge that the transaction will result in a
45 violation of this section. The Real Estate Commission shall establish the form for the affidavit
46 required under this subsection.
47 (g) Upon receipt of information that leads the Attorney General to believe that a
48 prohibited foreign party has not divested itself of the land described in subsection (a) of this
49 section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, as required under
50 subsection (e) of this section, the Attorney General shall enforce a violation of this section by
51 commencing a receivership proceeding in the county where the property or data center is situated
