21 REQUIREMENTS FOR UTILITY SERVICE CONTRACTS WITH DATA CENTERS
22 SECTION 4.(a) Article 7 of Chapter 62 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
23 a new section to read:
24 "§ 62-142.1. Contracts with data centers.
25 (a) Each data center located in North Carolina is required to enter into an electric service
26 contract with the electric public utility providing service to the data center. Each contract between
27 an electric public utility and a data center for the provision of electric service shall include terms
28 and conditions designed to (i) protect residential, other retail, and wholesale electricity customers
29 from costs incurred or reasonably anticipated to be incurred by the electric public utility to
30 provide electric service to the data center and (ii) prevent, to the maximum extent reasonably
31 feasible, other retail customers from subsidizing the cost of the data center's electric service. Such
32 contracts shall include all of the following:
33 (1) Minimum billing requirements designed to recover incremental costs
34 associated with serving or preparing to serve a data center.
35 (2) A contract term that is sufficient to recover all of the electric public utility's
36 incremental costs and which may exceed the length of the applicable service
37 tariff.
38 (3) Performance and credit provisions designed to protect retail customers in the
39 event of contract default.
40 (4) Termination provisions designed to protect retail customers in the event of
41 termination of the contract for electric service.
42 (b) Each contract between an electric public utility and a data center for the provision of
43 electric service shall be filed with the Commission as soon as practicable but in no event later
44 than 30 days from the date of contract execution by both parties. Either the utility or the data
45 center, or both, may designate all or any portion of a contract as confidential information as
46 defined in G.S. 132-1.2, or sensitive public security information as defined in G.S. 132-1.7.
47 Information shall be considered confidential only to the extent provided by law. Any dispute
48 about whether information has been properly designated as confidential shall be determined by
49 the Commission upon motion and response of interested parties. Subject to the requirements of
50 G.S. 62-34(c), the Public Staff shall have the right to examine confidential information, as well
Senate Bill 730-Fifth Edition Page 7

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 as sensitive public security information, in exercising any power or performing any duty
2 authorized by this Chapter.
3 (c) As part of the report required on the long-range needs for the expansion of facilities
4 for the generation of electricity pursuant to G.S. 62-110.1(c), the electric public utility shall
5 include details on contracted demand versus actual demand for each data center for the previous
6 three years.
7 (d) As used in this section, the term "data center" means a facility, campus of facilities,
8 or array of interconnected facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for the primary
9 purpose of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a peak monthly
10 electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater. The term "data center" does not include a facility
11 or portion of a facility containing electronic equipment that is incidental to and used in support
12 of a business whose primary business activity is not the storing, retrieving, managing, and
13 processing of digital data.
14 (e) The Commission may adopt rules to implement the requirements of this section.
15 Nothing in this section shall be construed to limit the authority of the Commission to adopt such
16 additional rules as are in the public interest to protect retail customers from costs incurred by
17 electric public utilities to provide electric service to data centers."
18 SECTION 4.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
19 agreements between an electric public utility and a data center entered into on or after that date.
