21 NO CONDEMNATION FOR DATA CENTERS
22 SECTION 5. Article 1 of Chapter 40A of the General Statutes is amended by adding
23 a new section to read:
24 "§ 40A-14. No condemnation to facilitate siting of data center.
25 Notwithstanding any authority granted under this Chapter, no condemnor shall exercise the
26 power of eminent domain for the purpose of acquiring land for a data center to be sited upon."
27
28 NO LOCAL GOVERNMENT INCENTIVES FOR DATA CENTERS
29 SECTION 6.(a) G.S. 158-7.1 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
30 "(i) Notwithstanding subsection (a), (b), or (d) of this section, local governments are
31 prohibited from providing any economic development incentives for siting of a data center within
32 their jurisdiction. For purposes of this section, the term "data center" means a facility, campus of
33 facilities, or array of interconnected facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for
34 the primary purpose of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a
35 peak monthly electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater. The term "data center" does not
36 include a facility or portion of a facility containing electronic equipment that is incidental to and
37 used in support of a business whose primary business activity is not the storing, retrieving,
38 managing, and processing of digital data."
39 SECTION 6.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to data
40 centers for which no local development approvals or State permits, certifications, or
41 authorizations have been issued for siting of the data center on or before that date. This section
42 shall not be construed to impair agreements for incentives executed on or before that date.
