44 PART II. ENERGY POLICY PROVISIONS
45
46 UTILITIES COMMISSION TO DELAY COMPLIANCE WITH CEPS REQUIREMENT
47 THROUGH USE OF SWINE WASTE RESOURCES FOR ELECTRIC MEMBERSHIP
48 CO-OPERATIVES AND MUNICIPAL ELECTRIC PROVIDERS
49 SECTION 7. The Utilities Commission shall delay the required compliance with
50 G.S. 62-133.8(e) by the Electric Membership Co-operatives and Municipal Electric Providers
51 (the Systems) until January 1, 2029, unless the systems request the ability to execute a contract
Page 8 Senate Bill 730-Fifth Edition

